sec.p:
There are two types of phototherapy treatment:
The standard phototherapy treatment (SPT), the bilirubin level is ≤ 300 μmol/l and the rate of the bilirubin should be reduced at about 25% within 24 h;
The intensive phototherapy treatment (IPT), the bilirubin level is > 300 μmol/l and the rate of the bilirubin should be reduced at about 50% within 24 h. The principle of the PT consists of lying the baby under the blue light (radiation) within a limited period according to the level of jaundice [5, 11]. The degree of absorption depends on the wavelength of the light [5, 11]. The absorption wavelength range is generally between 380 and 490 nm, centered at 459 nm [11]. The blue radiation for jaundice curing transforms the bilirubin in the skin of the baby and eliminates it through the urine and feces.

