The LED characteristics are following:
Luminosity flux: 13 lm per LED;
Diffusion angle: 120°;
Number of LED: 13;
Power supply voltage: 2.8–3.6 V;
Maximum current intensity: 350 mA. We have chosen to park the LEDs in wood box after taping in order to protect the LEDs from mechanical shock when transporting. The LEDs may be damaged if the boxes are dropped or receive a strong impact against them, so precautions must be taken to prevent any damage. The boxes are not water resistant and therefore must be kept away from water and moisture. The dimensions of the LEDs are 3.2 mm × 2.8 mm × 0.8 mm.

The properties of the designed apparatus are:
Power energy: 14 W;
Main supply voltage: (220–230) V;
Solar panel: 12 V;
Frequency: 50 Hz;
Irradiance: (6.68–25.81) µW/cm2;
wavelength: (440–470) nm with a peak at 458 ± 1 nm;
Operating temperature: 0–65 °C;
Height: 180 cm. Note that the values of the wavelength related to the spectral distribution and the brightness given above for the LEDs used in this work can be found in the datasheet of the supplier Kingbright electronic Europe [13]. The solar energy supply has been done following the practical principles of solar power supply and the use of solar panels in the houses.
